verbose_text: In cultured cortical neurons lacking p47 (phox), a cytosolic subunit of Nox, extensive N-methyl-D-aspartic acid (NMDA) receptor activation failed to produce ROS, while H 2 O 2 or the mitochondrial complex III inhibitor (antimycin) increased ROS [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: Nox, extensive N-methyl-D-aspartic acid (NMDA) receptor activation failed to produce ROS
